(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories New York - Authorities in New York City say a man has killed his grandmother and later left her body wrapped in a sheet on a Brooklyn street corner. Police say 70-year-old Joyce Spears' body was found near her Crown Heights home. An emergency medical services crew pronounced her dead at the scene.Investigators say a blood stained dumbbell and knife were found near the woman and police say an autopsy will be conducted.Police later arrested the woman's 32-year-old grandson, who shared a flat with his grandmother. He was charged with second-degree murder.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.